<br>
Ear:   +2 Agi ear ring(forget name, from black burrow)<br>
Ear:   Pollished bone hoop(+10 mana)<br>
Face: Cloth armor<br>
Neck: Chipped bone collar(4ac 10HP 10Mana)<br>
Head: Raw silk<br>
Arms: Hollowed bone bracer( 6ac +15 mana +7 Vs magic)<br>
Chest: Oracle Robe( +5 Int/Wis+25 mana 8ac-very ugly)<br>
Legs:  Raw silk<br>
Feet:  Raw Silk<br>
Back: nothing<br>
Waist: cloth<br>
Sholder: Cloth<br>
Hands: raw silk<br>
Finger: +2 int ring<br>
Finger: Adamantite band(75hp -10 Vs Magic)<br>
Wrist: Bracelet of Woven Grass(3 Int 12hp 1ac)<br>
Wrist: Bracelet of Woven Grass<br>
Melee 1: Dragoon Dirk(2 dex +3 vs magic)<br>
Melee 2: Stein of Moggok<br>
Range: Splitpaw eye(+2 vs poison)<br>
<br>
Thats all I think... I have around 500pp I could spend to upgrade some stuff..... any suggestions?<br>
<br>
Im sure you see posts like this alot, so thanks for any help <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sahhar>Sahhar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 9:43:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gear upgrades? </span><hr size=1> The ear &amp; neck slots seem to be easily upgradable for your budget at first glance. I think you should be able to purchase two +4 int +2 str earrings for well under 500pp or perhaps if a jeweler is feeling generous, you might be able to grab a velium sapphire necklace +7 int +7 str for around 500pp. Just my 2cp worth. I'm sure others might provide other avenues to pursue. Good luck!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urealwing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Realwing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ultradbz.net/buttons/mybutton.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 9:46:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gear upgrades? </span><hr size=1> Sell that oracle for 300 or so, then throw 200 plat into that, and buy yourself an advisor robe... do WHATEVER it takes to get out of that oracle ASAP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullaimpudu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>llaim Pudu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/01 12:24:14 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gear upgrades? </span><hr size=1> Look into some Obsidian Bead Hoops. Great earrings! They drop in Sol A and aren't too expensive. <p><img src="http://members.home.net/wax32/images/llaim.jpg" align=left><font face=arial size=2>Adventurers on Fennin Ro:<BR>llaim Pudu, 55 Halfling Templar<br>locust Pudu, 53 Halfling Rake<br>Illnuu 31 Gnome Wizard<br><br><a href="http://frontpage.home.net/wax32/">The Pudu Brothers' Signpost</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=branaman>Branaman</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/01 12:40:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gear upgrades? </span><hr size=1> Hmm, if you are near Quenos. Jump in the sewers and kill Cubert for some +3 int earrings. Andmaybe a rodchet band can help out. Visit Chandra miller for some Bear hide shoes/armor. And auction for a cloak of the icebear by the barbarians. The sv vs cold comes in handy if you ever want to raid that Vox.<br>
<br>
Hmm, if you still wear cloth, get the dust of your tailoring kit and sew some silk together. <p><center><img src="http://home.soneraplaza.nl/qn/prive/ja.wensveen/Branaman2.jpg" width="500" alt="" border="0" align="center"><br><table><tr>
