Branaman Starbinder <Hated Ones > <BR>
50th Dark Elf Wizard on Prexus.</center></font></font></td>
</tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=machival>Machival</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/01 12:59:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gear upgrades? </span><hr size=1> Yes, for those ears, find someone to make you some golden sapphire earrings (2 str, 4 int) For your head you can find a Savant's Cap (3 wis 3 int) for around 20-30pp (The batfang headband is the exact same stats, but people usually want a few hundred pp for it, dont get tricked) For your face, see if you can aquire a sheer bone mask (3 ac, 3 int), shouldnt be too expensive. If you have a little extra money, you can try to upgrade your rings to platinum star rose rings (4 int each) or if you have a friend who is good in jewlecraft. Thats about all you can get if you spend your money wisely, theres lots of decent +int gear on velious, but thats for 30+<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
Machival Winterlong<br>
Lanys T'Vyl<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/01 1:51:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/sigpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gear upgrades? </span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Sell that oracle for 300 or so, then throw 200 plat into that, and buy yourself an advisor robe... do WHATEVER it takes to get out of that oracle ASAP.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Oracle robes are great robes at level 18. Hell, they're an awesome robe at that level. In fact, they're probably as good as the Advisor robe. Unless you need magic Resist, stick with the Oracle Robe.<br>
<br>
Someone your level should start working on getting their Temple of Sol Ro stuff. Acumen Mask, Runescale Cloak, SoTF, Tishan's Kilt. Maybe start doing the Staff of the wheel quest.<br>
<br>
Save your money! At level 18, I'd say you're doing better than most, and you'll find upgrades when you least expect them. <p><center><IMG SRC=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarnin3dsig.jpg><br><center><Br><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging<Br><Br><b>DEATH TO AL`KABOR!</b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulummanaburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LumManaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/01 3:21:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gear upgrades? </span><hr size=1> First of all, DONT waste money getting an advisor robe. The Oracle Robe is a great robe, especially for someone of your level. <br>
<br>
My suggestions are...<br>
<br>
Head - Savants Cap +3 int, goes for around 30p<br>
Ears - + 3 INT Quest in Qeynos.<br>
Hands - Dusty Bloodstained. +25 mana, goes for around 30p or so. Been wearing mine since low 20s. <br>
Feet, Back &amp; Belt -  Wolf hide or Bear hide quest in Qeynos Hills. See the Quest Section on Graffes page for details.<br>
Legs - Raw silk is fine. Mammoth Hide leggings will give you better AC and can be bought for around 30p. I wore those until I got my Carmine Pants.<br>
Shoulder - Frozen mantle (AC 6, 10 mana), goes for around 50p.<br>
<br>
Those items should help you a bunch, and are not very expenseive so they fit your budget. At 18 I was wearing similar gear as yourself.  Try to focus on smaller items then spending hundreds of plat on one item. <br>
<br>
Just my 2 copper.<br>
<br>
